steps I would say,

00:14:07.890 --> 00:14:09.540 align:middle line:84%
and then making
sure that you do--

00:14:09.540 --> 00:14:13.680 align:middle line:84%
actually, make sure you do have
a good quality source fats.

00:14:13.680 --> 00:14:16.260 align:middle line:84%
Fats are something that has
been demonized for years.

00:14:16.260 --> 00:14:18.240 align:middle line:84%
Even when I was at
medical college,

00:14:18.240 --> 00:14:19.770 align:middle line:90%
saturated fats are bad for you.

00:14:19.770 --> 00:14:22.950 align:middle line:84%
Polyunsaturated, plant-based
oils are good for you.

00:14:22.950 --> 00:14:24.930 align:middle line:84%
Now we know that the
complete reverse,

00:14:24.930 --> 00:14:27.300 align:middle line:84%
and actually, we should
be encouraging people

00:14:27.300 --> 00:14:28.800 align:middle line:84%
to look at the
quality of their fats

00:14:28.800 --> 00:14:32.370 align:middle line:84%
rather than the quantities
of monounsaturated

00:14:32.370 --> 00:14:34.500 align:middle line:84%
versus saturated fats
and all the rest of it.

00:14:34.500 --> 00:14:38.740 align:middle line:84%
So nuts, seeds, beans, oils,
extra-virgin olive oil,

00:14:38.740 --> 00:14:40.980 align:middle line:84%
